{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Histone PARylation factor 1 (HPF1, previously known as C4orf27) is a key regulator of ADP-ribosylation signaling in response to DNA damage. It has been demonstrated that HPF1 forms a complex with PARP-1 (poly(ADP-ribose) polymerase 1) and is recruited to DNA lesions in a PARP-1-dependent manner, but independently of PARP-1 catalytic ADP-ribosylation activity. HPF1 has also been shown limit DNA damage-induced hyper-automodification of PARP-1 by promoting PARP-1-dependent in trans ADP-ribosylation of histones [[cite:PUB00081458]]. This protein is essential for Ser-ADPr (ADPr on serine residues), which represents the major fraction of ADPr synthesised after DNA damage [[cite:PUB00101317]]. HPF1, which shows an α-β structure with two tightly-associated domains connected via an elaborate linker, forms a composite active site with PARP-1 [[cite:PUB00101318], [cite:PUB00101316]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "6m3h", "name" "Crystal structure of mouse HPF1"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF10228" "Histone PARylation factor 1"}, "panther" {"PTHR13386" "HISTONE PARYLATION FACTOR 1"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Histone PARylation factor 1", "short" "HPF1"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 10, "domain_architectures" 41, "proteomes" 1024, "taxa" 4154, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1977, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1881, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1301}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR019361", :literature {"PUB00081458" {"URL" nil, "issue" "3", "authors" ["Gibbs-Seymour I" "Fontana P" "Rack JG" "Ahel I."], "ISO_journal" "Mol. Cell", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.molcel.2016.03.008", "medline_journal" "Mol Cell", "title" "HPF1/C4orf27 Is a PARP-1-Interacting Protein that Regulates PARP-1 ADP-Ribosyl